<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2310] CassandraStorage for pig checks for environment variable on mappers/reducers, but it should only need to be set on the machine launching pig.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2310</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Only error out if necessary pig settings have not previously been set in job config. CassandraStorage checks for environment variables on mappers/reducers, but it should only need to be set on the machine launching the pig jobs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12501053">CASSANDRA-2310</key>
            <summary>CassandraStorage for pig checks for environment variable on mappers/reducers, but it should only need to be set on the machine launching pig.</summary>
