                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13005263" author="eldondev" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 19:15:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the environment variable is set, it wins. If not, and it&apos;s already stored in the job configuration, do nothing. If it doesn&apos;t exist at all, fail.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005275" author="jeromatron" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 19:30:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 - works where before it would error out in mapreduce mode (post storefunc). I did suggest maybe unifying the conditions and using an else or something to make it more concise, but that&apos;s a trivial thing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005325" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 20:47:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005474" author="hudson" created="Fri, 11 Mar 2011 03:47:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #373 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/373/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/373/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
